# How to Show Dialogue

## To show an instructional prompt:
```
StartCoroutine(DialogeManager.Instance.InstructionalText(string text, float duration));
```


Definitions:
string text = text we want to display in the dialogue box
duration = how long to display text before it fades out

## To run character dialogue:
```string[] lines = {```
``` "Lines part 1.```
``` "Lines part 2."```
```};```
```StartCoroutine(DialogueManager.Instance.CharacterDialogue(string characterName, lines));```
```DialogueManager.Instance.typeSpeed = 0.02f;```

Definitions:
characterName = name of character speaking
lines = each element in array displays using CharacterDialogue coroutine
typeSpeed = declare a float to increase or decrease typeSpeed. smaller time is faster type

## To show a narration:

```StartCoroutine(DialogueManager.Instance.Narration("Narration...", float duration));```

"Narration..." = narration to display
duration = how long narration is displayed before it is hidden

